  <fishFact>k__BackingField: "When threatened, pufferfish rapidly gulp water to inflate
    themselves into a spiky balloon \u2014 making them nearly impossible to swallow.
    As if that weren't enough, most species are also highly toxic. Yet in Japan,
    pufferfish (called fugu) is considered a delicacy, prepared only by specially
    licensed chefs. "
